nd others, many people reach the limits of their strength. What seems like an individual failure regarding everyday requirements is a result of neo-liberal crisis management. A fundamental change of perspective is necessary: a Care Revolution. Gabriele Winter develops steps towards a caring society that no longer focuses on maximizing profit, but on human needs and especially on caring for each other - for a world in which people are no longer pitted against each other in competition, but can jointly shape their individual lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aArbeit. 4aCare. 4aFeminismus. 4aGender Studies. 4aGender. 4aGesellschaft. 4aKrise. 4aPflege. 4aPolitik. 4aSorge. 4aSoziale Bewegung. 4aSozialpolitik. 4aSoziologie. 4aZivilgesellschaft. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aCare.  aCivil Society.  aCrisis.  aFeminism.  aGender Studies.  aGender.  aPolitics.  aSocial Movement.  aSocial Policy.  aSociety.  aSociology.  aWork.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2015z9783110438741oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070099208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839430408zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839430408423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839430408/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-070099-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2015b